gmx:name.gco:CharacterString: Feature catalog for Intermediate Discharges into Near Coastal Marine Waters: Southern California, 2003

gmx:scope.gco:CharacterString: Sewage; Drainage; Marine pollution; Watersheds; Coasts

gfc:definition.gco:CharacterString: Shapefile Attribute Table
Area of feature in internal units squared.
Internal feature number.
This is the name of the discharger that has primary responsibility over the outfall
Internal feature number.
Internal feature number.
This is the facility operated by the primary discharger which contributes effluent to the outfall.
This is the regional board region by number in which the outfall exists. (North Coast =1, San Francisco Bay = 2, Central Coast = 3, Los Angeles =4, Santa Ana = 8, San Diego = 9 )
Internal feature number.
This is a qualitative description of the effluent discharged to the outfall from the primary discharger.
This is the longitude of the outfall
This is the latitude of the outfall
This is the depth of the outfall below sea level (mean lower low water) in feet

This is the total flow rate in millions of gallons per day (MGD) for the combined effluent from primary and secondary dischargers for the outfall. The total flow rate = the primary discharger's flow rate + the contributing discharger's flow rate
This is the flowrate in millions of gallons per day (MGD) for the effluent from the primary discharger.
This is the rating assigned to the primary discharge (major discharge or minor discharge). The rating is assigned to the discharge and not the outfall
This is the flowrate in millions of gallons per day (MGD) for the effluent from the contributing discharger
This is the rating assigned to the contributing discharge (major discharge or minor discharge). The rating is assigned to the discharge and not the outfall.
Internal feature number.
This is the street address of the office of the contributing discharger
This is the zip code of the office of the contributing discharger
This is the street address or location of the contributing discharger's facility (i.e., the facility that generates or releases the waste).
This is the city in which the contributing discharger's facility is located.
This is the zip code of the office of the contributing discharger's facility
